[07:55.01]GRATIANO	[To NERISSA] By yonder moon I swear you do me wrong;
[07:58.67]	In faith, I gave it to the judge's clerk:
[08:01.98]	Would he were gelt that had it, for my part,
[08:05.50]	Since you do take it, love, so much at heart.
[08:09.02]PORTIA	A quarrel, ho, already! what's the matter?
[08:12.26]GRATIANO	About a hoop of gold, a paltry ring
[08:15.20]	That she did give me, whose posy was
[08:18.22]	For all the world like cutler's poetry
[08:21.46]	Upon a knife, 'Love me, and leave me not.'
[08:24.62]NERISSA	What talk you of the posy or the value?
[08:27.85]	You swore to me, when I did give it you,
[08:31.09]	That you would wear it till your hour of death
[08:34.90]	And that it should lie with you in your grave:
[08:38.64]	Though not for me, yet for your vehement oaths,
[08:42.37]	You should have been respective and have kept it.
[08:46.33]	Gave it a judge's clerk! no, God's my judge,
