[08:54.02]GRATIANO	He will, an if he live to be a man.
[08:56.89]NERISSA	Ay, if a woman live to be a man.
[08:59.55]GRATIANO	Now, by this hand, I gave it to a youth,
[09:02.71]	A kind of boy, a little scrubbed boy,
[09:05.73]	No higher than thyself; the judge's clerk,
[09:09.11]	A prating boy, that begg'd it as a fee:
[09:12.27]	I could not for my heart deny it him.
[09:15.36]PORTIA	You were to blame, I must be plain with you,
[09:18.88]	To part so slightly with your wife's first gift:
[09:22.77]	A thing stuck on with oaths upon your finger
